<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Italy-Crime     01-26 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Italy-Crime,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Bust Crime Ring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>REGGIO DI CALABRIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police cracked down on a
Calabria crime ring and arrested at least 44 people on homicide,
arms trafficking and other charges, authorities say.
   Police had warrants for the arrest of 61 people. Two already were
jailed on other charges prior to Wednesday's arrests and the rest
were being sought.
   Those arrested were charged with criminal association and some
were charged in connection with 18 homicides, drug and arms
trafficking, kidnapping and extortion, the Italian news agency AGI
said.
   Among the fugitives was Giuseppe Pesce, the reputed head of the
mob based in the Rosarno area of the province of Reggio di Calabria,
at the southern tip of Italy.
</TEXT>
