<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--FirstCrash     01-26 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--First Crash,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>95-Year-Old Driver Has First Accident After 65 Years _ Hits Squad
Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VILLA RICA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ninety-five-year-old Horace E. Nunley had
been driving 65 years before he had his first accident: He hit a
Georgia State Patrol car, authorities said.
   Neither Nunley nor Trooper Douglas H. Ralston, 38, was seriously
injured in Wednesday's crash.
   Nunley's car sustained front-end damage and the patrol car was
damaged on a side, according to police.
   Nunley was listed in good condition Wednesday afternoon at Tanner
Medical Center.
   ``I'm sore on my right side from my shoulder to my hip,'' Nunley
said. ``I'm mostly bruised up.''
   Asked if he planned to replace his car or drive again, Nunley
replied, ``Not any time soon.''
</TEXT>
