<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--WrongCremation     01-26 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Wrong Cremation,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Father Lives, But Who Was Cremated?</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bereaved family held a funeral
service and cremated a body they thought was their father _ then
learned he was still alive, a newspaper reported today.
   ``We do not know who we cremated,'' Subramaniam Nadarajah was
quoted as saying in the New Straits Times daily.
   Nadarajah and his two sisters went to a hospital mortuary at
Sungei Petani and identified a body there as that of their missing
father, Nadarajah, the newspaper reported.
   On Tuesday, 200 people attended his funeral, followed by the
cremation.
   A few hours later a friend of Subramaniam's said he spotted the
father at a Hindu temple. The family rushed to the temple and found
their father, praying.
   The newspaper said the father was missing for seven weeks and
apparently had been admitted to a mental hospital, then released.
   Police said they should be able to identify the dead man.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
