<FIRST>u i AM-Japan-Markets     01-26 0186</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar Closes Slightly Lower Against Yen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar closed slightly lower against the
Japanese yen Thursday, while share prices lost ground on the Tokyo
Stock Exchange.
   The dollar opened at 127.37 yen, down 0.28 yen from Wednesday's
close of 127.65 yen, and traded in a tight range of 127.33 -.60
before closing at 127.52 yen, down 0.13 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which gained 10.11 points for a record 31,567.79
points Wednesday, dipped 55.98 points, or 0.18 percent, to close at
31,511.81 points.
   Exchange dealers said the dollar's bearishness in Tokyo reflected
an overnight decline in New York amid intervention by the Federal
Reserve.
   One dealer said anxiety about possible intervention by the Bank
of Japan to push the dollar down was also reflected in the
currency's weakness. Trading otherwise was relatively quiet, he said.
   On the stock exchange, the market's main economic barometer edged
down as a result of profit taking.
   ``Many investors sat out today from the fear of higher interest
rates,'' said a dealer at Nikko Securities Co.
</TEXT>
