<HEAD>Thieves Grab Shark Fins in Seafood Caper</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thieves feeding a market voracious for exotic
food stole more than 1,000 pounds of shark fins, an ingredient in a
popular soup, authorities said Thursday.
   The fins, worth about $64,000, were stolen from The Shu Kee
Seafood Store in Hong Kong, said a police spokesman.
   A bowl of shark's fin soup, which some believe can help preserve
youth, can cost up to $35.
   In August, thieves took 156 pounds of bird's nests worth
$134,000. The nests, which are made from the saliva of swallows, are
considered a health food particularly favored by the elderly.
