<HEAD>Frustrated Victim Posts Reward</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINGSPORT, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A victim of car theft is offering a
$1,000 reward to the first person in the next two weeks to help
catch a local car thief _ any local car thief.
   Scott Thomsen of Blountville said he decided to put up the money
after police informed him the odds are slim they'll find the person
who stole and torched his car Jan. 21.
   ``What inspired me was the people down at the police department
said the only possibility of catching these guys was a reward,'' he
said.
   Thomsen said his offer, made Wednesday, is only good for the next
two weeks and only if the information leads to a conviction in any
Kingsport auto theft case.
   Police Detective Doug Harris said car thieves looking for a quick
way to get somewhere often burn cars to destroy any physical
evidence.
