cooperation.
   Stanton's withdrawal narrowed the field to Brown and former Rep.
Jim Jones of Oklahoma.
   Brown virtually locked up the post Wednesday when Michigan
Democratic Party chairman Richard Wiener withdrew and endorsed
Brown. Brown and Wiener were regarded as the two leading contenders
for the post which will be filled by the national committee on Feb.
10.
   Paul G. Kirk Jr., party chairman since 1985, declined to seek
another four-year term.
