<DATELINE>MATTOON, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 125-acre plot of farmland once owned by
Abraham Lincoln and his father was sold at auction Thursday to a
farmer for $98,500.
   Ron Best, a Coles County farmer, beat two other bidders at a
foreclosure sale held in Mattoon. Best's purchase will be used to
retire a mortgage signed by Raymond W. Phipps of Springfield in
August 1975.
