   Congress wasted little time sticking a pin into
President Bush's trial balloon suggesting that depositors pay for
rescuing the savings and loan industry.
   Bush's Treasury secretary, Nicholas F. Brady, said Wednesday his
staff is looking into a variety of revenue-raising options,
including a proposal to charge depositors in banks, S&amp;Ls and credit
unions a 25-cent fee for every $100 in their accounts.
   Bush, in an interview, stressed that he hasn't made any
