   Prime Minister Noboru Takeshita says he won't be
driven from office by a stock-trading scandal that has forced three
Cabinet ministers to resign, and will try to restore public trust in
government.
   Takeshita's comments Wednesday came in response to opposition
demands for his removal after Ken Harada, the Economic Planning
Agency director, resigned because of links to the Recruit Co.
conglomerate, the company involved.
