<HEAD>Production Up this Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
252,260 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
246,728, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 214,352 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 158,083 cars this week,
compared with 153,472 a week ago and 128,433 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 94,177,
compared with last week's 93,256 and last year's 85,919.
   Canadian automakers were to build 21,095 cars this week, up from
19,811 a week ago but down from last year's 22,579.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,515, compared
with 21,741 a week ago and 20,453 in the same week last year.
