<HEAD>Farley Extends Tender Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Farley Inc. announced today that it is extending
for the ninth time its $1.4 billion hostile takeover bid for
Georgia-based West Point-Pepperell, Inc.
   The new deadline is midnight Feb. 1, a week later than the
earlier Jan. 25 deadline, Farley said in a statement.
   About 15.7 million shares of West Point-Pepperell common stock
had been tendered by shareholders as of the close of business
Wednesday, which gives Farley approximately 62 percent of Pepperell
common stock, the company said.
   Chicago-based Farley, maker of Fruit of the Loom underwear and
Acme boots, first made its $48-per-share cash offer Oct. 25 to
acquire Pepperell, the nation's largest publicly held textile
company.
   Pepperell, based in West Point, Ga., has been battling the
takeover in court.
   Farley also said a special Pepperell shareholders meeting is
scheduled Feb. 25, when Farley will seek to oust current Pepperell
directors.
