<FIRST>r f AM-DeanWitter     01-26 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Dean Witter,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dean Witter Restructuring Operations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dean Witter Financial Services Group said
Thursday it was restructuring its businesses to create separate
divisions for its sales and product development operations.
   The new divisions are Dean Witter Financial, which encompasses
the company's sales and marketing staff and includes branch offices
and trading operations; Dean Witter Capital, which will include
investment banking, asset management and Dean Witter's realty
business; and Discover Card, the firm's credit card operation.
   James Flynn, a Dean Witter spokesman, said the reshuffling was
unrelated to the restructuring announced recently by the company's
parent, Sears, Roebuck and Co. Sears said it would overhaul its
retail business and focus on the consumer side of its financial
service segment.
   The spokesman said there would not be any charges against Sears'
earnings related to the Dean Witter restructuring, nor would there
be any layoffs.
   ``Longer-term it will save us some money,'' Flynn said. ``It
hopefully will make us more profitable.''
   Flynn said the company expected other big investment firms to
similarly restructure their operations.
</TEXT>
