<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-DuPont     01-26 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Du Pont,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Du Pont Earnings Up 14 Percent In 1988 Fouth Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Du Pont Co. on Thursday said
fourth-quarter earnings were up 14 percent over the same quarter the
previous year, while earnings for the year were up 23 percent.
   Net income for the fourth quarter was $500 million, or $2.08 a
share, compared with $439 million, or $1.82 a share, in the same
1987 quarter. Sales for the quarter were up 6 percent at $8.4
billion from $7.9 billion in the 1987 fourth quarter.
   For the full year, Du Pont reported $2.2 billion in earnings, or
$9.11 a share, up 23 percent from $1.8 billion, or $7.39 a share.
Sales for 1988 were $32.9 billion, up 8 percent from $30.5 billion
in 1987.
   ``We are pleased to report a third consecutive year of earnings
growth, reflecting generally strong worldwide demand,'' Du Pont
Chairman Richard E. Heckert said.
   Heckert attributed the earnings rise to strong performances in
petroleum refining, agricultural and industrial chemicals, polymer
products, coal and fibers segments.
</TEXT>
