<HEAD>Crude Runs Up Last Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude runs to stills averaged 13,524,000
barrels daily during the week ended Friday, Jan. 20, the American
Petroleum Institute reported Thursday. This compared with 13,486,000
barrels daily in the previous week and 12,943,000 barrels daily a
year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,886,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,814,000 the previous week and 10,430,000 a year ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
7,225,000 barrels a day, compared with 7,116,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,774,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 6,040,000 a day
compared with 5,862,000 a day last week and 5,647,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
236,396,000 barrels, versus 234,376,000 a week earlier and
234,887,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 202,413,000
barrels compared with 200,483,000 in the previous week and
203,386,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production for
the week ended Friday was 7,913,000 barrels compared with 8,211,000
last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 326,228,000 barrels at the close of last
week, against 324,211,000 a week previous and 341,238,000 a year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 247,577,000 barrels,
compared with 249,371,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 4,892,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 890,000, distillate
fuel oil, 213,O00, and others 1,661,000, a total of 7,656,000
barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 255,000 barrels, and products
67,000, a total of 322,000 barrels, for a grand total of 7,978,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 4,926,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 498,000, distillate fuel
oil 173,000, and others 682,000, for a total of 7,690,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 199,000 barrels, products 69,000, a total of 268,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 7,958,000.
